memberdef.name: rocblas_gemm_ex

detaileddescription.para: GEMM_EX performs one of the matrix-matrix operations D = alpha*op( A )*op( B ) + beta*C,
where op( X ) is one of op( X ) = X or op( X ) = X**T or op( X ) = X**H,
alpha and beta are scalars, and A, B, C, and D are matrices, with op( A ) an m by k matrix, op( B ) a k by n matrix and C and D are m by n matrices.

parameterdescription.para: rocblas_handle. handle to the rocblas library context queue.
rocblas_operation specifies the form of op( A )
rocblas_operation specifies the form of op( B )
rocblas_int. matrix dimension m
rocblas_int. matrix dimension n
rocblas_int. matrix dimension k
const void * specifies the scalar alpha. Same datatype as compute_type.
void * pointer storing matrix A on the GPU.
rocblas_datatype specifies the datatype of matrix A
rocblas_int specifies the leading dimension of A.
void * pointer storing matrix B on the GPU.
rocblas_datatype specifies the datatype of matrix B
rocblas_int specifies the leading dimension of B.
const void * specifies the scalar beta. Same datatype as compute_type.
void * pointer storing matrix C on the GPU.
rocblas_datatype specifies the datatype of matrix C
rocblas_int specifies the leading dimension of C.
void * pointer storing matrix D on the GPU.
rocblas_datatype specifies the datatype of matrix D
rocblas_int specifies the leading dimension of D.
rocblas_datatype specifies the datatype of computation
rocblas_gemm_algo enumerant specifying the algorithm type.
int32_t reserved for future use
uint32_t reserved for future use

memberdef.name: rocblas_gemm_strided_batched_ex

detaileddescription.para: GEMM_STRIDED_BATCHED_EX performs one of the strided_batched matrix-matrix operations D[i*stride_d] = alpha*op(A[i*stride_a])*op(B[i*stride_b]) + beta*C[i*stride_c], for i in [0,batch_count-1]
where op( X ) is one of op( X ) = X or op( X ) = X**T or op( X ) = X**H,

alpha and beta are scalars, and A, B, C, and D are strided_batched matrices, with op( A ) an m by k by batch_count strided_batched matrix, op( B ) a k by n by batch_count strided_batched matrix and C and D are m by n by batch_count strided_batched matrices.
The strided_batched matrices are multiple matrices separated by a constant stride. The number of matrices is batch_count.
